article.description: Justin Robinson scored a career-high 28 points and Rider led all the way in defeating Southern California 77-57 in an opening game of the Hall of Fame Classic on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Rider hands USC its first loss in wall-to-wall win
article.linkText: Rider hands USC its first loss in wall-to-wall win
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Justin Robinson scored a career-high 28 points and Rider led all the way in defeating Southern California 77-57 in an opening game of the Hall of Fame Classic on Wednesday night. Novar Gadson added 10 points for the Broncs (2-1), who shot 60 percent from the floor, 63 percent from long-range and 73 percent at the line. Robinson made all 5 of his 3-pointers, tying his career high. USC had no answer for Robinson, who also was perfect from the line, going 5 for 5. The senior from London, England, made his 94th career start, making him one of the most experienced point guards in Division I. The Trojans (2-1) were led by Maurice Jones and Donte Smith with 13 points each. Their usually reliable front line of Alex Stepheson and Nikola Vucevic were held to a combined 18 points.
